##Cluster of hospital-acquired infections in several countries

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Journalists Hu Zhenqing and Yan Songyang, thepaper.cn

The epidemic of new crown pneumonia is spreading in many countries. Due to the high density of susceptible population, nursing institutions and hospitals in South Korea, the United States and other countries have developed new crown pneumonia cluster infection. More than elderly people died from new crown pneumonia infection in a nursing center in the United States. Federal agencies have stepped in to investigate.

Patients or the elderly in long-term care institutions and hospitals are at higher risk of death from new pneumonia due to low immunity and underlying diseases. At the same time, infection or isolation of health-care workers may result in a shortage of staff and adversely affect the health-care system.

High mortality under special conditions

A new cluster of pneumonia infections has emerged in a long-term Care facility called Life Care Center in Kirkland, King County, Washington, CNN, Thursday. According to the New York Times, eight of the new pneumonia deaths in the United States have come from here. "Life Care Center" is a chain of nursing companies in the United States, in more than states have opened care centers to provide old age, rehabilitation, patient care and other services.

The Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services announced Friday that it will send inspectors to work with CDC experts to investigate whether the care center is complying with regulations to prevent infectious diseases.

All residents and those associated with them at this time, Kirkland said in a statement Tuesday, those with fever, cough and shortness of breath in particular "will continue to be under close observation" and family visits have been suspended.

CNN reported that the son of a resident of the nursing home tested positive for the new coronavirus. As the nursing home has not tested all the residents for the new coronavirus, the families of some residents expressed concern, we'd like to test the occupants and their families.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot of Youtube video of Kirkland's Life Care Center

In addition, The New York Times reported on Feb. 3 that the first death from new pneumonia in a life-care Center was transferred from the facility to Harborview Medical Center in Seattle on Feb. 24 and died two days later, he was diagnosed with a new coronavirus on March 3.

"More than 50 health care workers are now being tested for the virus on a daily basis as they treat patients without protection, " said Susan Gregg, a spokeswoman for the hospital, relatives and friends of 108 haberview hospital patients have been quarantined. The King County government is understood to be planning to buy a motel to isolate the confirmed cases.

The New York Times analysis suggests that the new coronavirus may have been circulating in Washington state or elsewhere for some time, but that perhaps the infected person's symptoms were not severe enough to be detected, allowing the virus to continue to spread. However, new coronary pneumonia is more dangerous in older people with underlying diseases. Most of the deaths in Washington state are over the age of 70, according to NPR.

In addition, a staff member at Valley Medical Center in Renton, Wash. , has been diagnosed with the new coronavirus, and 19 other staff members at the facility have been tested for the virus, which is temporarily negative.

Previously, South Korea's gyeongsang-do-seongdo-gyeongdo-gyeongnam hospital also had a large-scale infection incident, as of March 2, the hospital-related cases reached 119, with 7 deaths, of the 102 psychiatric inpatients, 99 were confirmed. The funeral of Lee Man-Hee's brother, founder of the New World Church, was held at Nant-le-grand Hospital in early February, and most of the confirmed cases in South Korea have been linked to the church.

Yonhap believes that the psychiatric inpatient area closed management of the particularity and hospital response lag, resulting in the spread of the virus in the hospital speed and scale out of control. According to The Washington Post, some South Korean experts pointed out that the hospital psychiatric inpatient conditions are poor, closed windows, poor ventilation, and patients with low immunity.

Are there more cluster infections?

Spain, Australia, the United Kingdom and other countries have also emerged care institutions and members of parliament infected, and many cases may be "local transmission" rather than imported cases. There are concerns about whether clusters of infections are also occurring in these places.

Ten residents and one staff member at a nursing home in the Spanish capital Madrid were confirmed to have the new coronavirus, the health department said on March 5, Reuters reported, one of them, a 99-year-old man, has died. All residents of the facility will be tested for the new coronavirus and activities will be suspended. At the same time, care institutions in the Madrid area will take a series of preventive measures.

By the morning of March 6, four elderly people and two staff members at the Dorothy Henderson Lodge in Sydney, Australia, had been diagnosed with the new coronavirus, according to a review of UK and Australian media.

On 4 March, health authorities confirmed that a 95-year-old man who had also died in the Care Centre on 3 March had contracted the new coronavirus.

There have also been cases of patients being infected in hospitals in the UK. Two patients at King's College Hospital in London have been diagnosed with the new coronavirus, the BBC reported Friday. A family member said the two confirmed patients had been in the same room. At present, the hospital has closed part of the hospital, staff and visitors restricted access to the confirmed cases used ward, and began to track the two cases of close contacts. A patient at a hospital in Manchester, northern England, was also confirmed to have the new coronavirus, the Daily Telegraph of London reported Thursday.

UK health officials have expressed concern about the cases because they have not travelled to high-risk countries and have not been in contact with other confirmed cases.

Isolation of medical staff or shortage of staff

Infection of health-care workers occurs in some countries at the same time as the patient is infected, which may lead to a shortage of health-care workers and adversely affect the response to the epidemic.

Five health care workers at two hospitals in the northern Spanish city of Basque Country have been infected with the new coronavirus and about 100 others are being quarantined, Spanish newspaper El Pais reported Wednesday. The hospital has ordered the The Adventure of the Resident Patient to stay in the ward and allow only one relative to visit.

In addition, the governments of Madrid and the Andalucía, Colombia have asked more than 200 health care workers who have come into contact with confirmed cases to stay at home to prevent hospital transmission of the virus.

Spain's health minister on the 3rd has proposed to cancel the recent medical conference, to ensure that medical staff.

According to the "Guardian" and "Sydney Morning Herald" News, New South Wales, Australia, 4 also confirmed at least 2 doctors infected with the new coronavirus, one of whom was diagnosed after contact with the new coronavirus infection. More than 80 staff at the two hospitals where the two doctors work are reported to be in isolation at home for 14 days.

New South Wales Health Officer CLEA Chanter said hospital staff were already available to support affected hospitals, but many needed to work overtime. She added that the hospital will be very busy at the moment because of the flu.
